    <note>Xu(3) Yuanyu [19624] He served in the administration of Li(2) Yu(5) [3551], last ruler of the Southern Tang, and returned to allegiance with Yu and was given a position in the Song government. Yuanyu probably moved to Yangzhou where he died in office and was buried in the Dazhong xiangfu period (1008-1016). His son, Tianxi [19625], moved to Changzhou, Wujin county, and this branch of Xu(3) Wen's [19615] descendants ended up as Changzhou residents in Song. Zeng Gong, WJ, 44.4a-5a. CBD, 3, 2020.</note>
